data.shownotes: The legendary inaugural Goosemas event. Jon bought dozens of pizzas, trays of tenders, salad, and more, and maybe ten or twelve kegs. Bonnie and a good friend held down the bar. data.shownotes: Strokin' was played for the first time since September 1, 2019 (89 shows) and was dedicated to the Trash Angels and Flavortown crew. Before Look Out Cleveland, a cake was brought out to celebrate the one-year anniversary of Jeff's first show in the band. At the beginning of the encore, another cake was brought out for Marta's birthday and the crowd sang to her.
The Way It Is was dedicated to Rich and Warren. During Bingo Tour Theme, Coach presented tickets to Fred: The Festival to the Coach Look-Alike contest winners by knighting them with the rainstick.

data.jamchart_notes: Laid-back jam with serious "Welcome to Delta" hints from Peter. Foreshadows where the song will go in 2022.
Delta jam bounces along to a great peak before Rick pops a string and Peter leads the rest of the band into a spooky and haunting motif that acts as the intro to "Dr. Darkness".
The band is in no hurry and really explores every inch of the Delta motif before descending into evil space, setting up "Dr. Darkness".

data.jamchart_notes: Pokes and prods at the edges of the "Delta" jam before finally breaking into a warm major-key motif that winds up back in the Indie-Groove "Atlas Dogs" progression. Great early summer evening jam.
